FT  15 SEP 93 / International Company News In Brief: New York Post
MR RUPERT Murdoch yesterday cleared the last remaining hurdle in his battle
to buy the ailing New York Post newspaper when a federal bankruptcy court
judge gave final approval for the purchase, writes Martin Dickson in New
York.
News Corporation, the media company headed by Mr Murdoch, said the sale
should be completed by the end of September. News Corporation is paying more
than Dollars 25m in cash for the Post and assuming its debt and liabilities.
